column1: #Text=Responsibilities: Design and build applications for the iOS platform.

#Text=Knowledge of Apple's design principles and application interface guidelines Unit-test code for robustness, including edge cases, usability, and general reliability Key Skills: Experience in Objective-C, Swift, Xcode, and Cocoa Touch Knowledge of iOS back-end services Proficient in iOS Frameworks such as Core Data, Core Graphics, and Core Animation Knowledge of Apple's design principles and application interface guidelines Responsibilities: Design and build applications for the iOS platform Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features Help maintain code quality, organization, and automatization Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize development efficiency
